# Core Invariants

## Architecture
- Hexagonal: domain layer has ZERO Spring/framework imports
- Layer order: `domain` ← `application` ← `adapter/{in,out}`
- No cross-service DB access — use events or REST API calls

## Dependency Rules
- Constructor injection ONLY — never `@Autowired` on field
- Domain entities never extend JPA entities — map in adapter/out/persistence
- DTOs are `record` types — immutable, no setters

## Persistence
- Spring Data JPA is the ONLY ORM (ADR-002)
- All schema changes MUST have a Flyway migration script
- Repository interfaces live in `adapter/out/persistence/`

## Events
- SQS FIFO for all inter-service messaging (ADR-001)
- Event class names: `{Entity}{PastTense}Event` e.g. `OrderCreatedEvent`
- Event fields: `eventId` (UUID), `occurredAt` (Instant), `aggregateId` (String)

## Workflow Reminder
Before writing code: check Context Routing in `AGENTS.md`.
After writing code: confirm the relevant capability `.mdc` checklist passes.
